Pre-Game Insights: Botswana were aiming for back-to-back wins and a spot in AFCON after a recent win streak.
Cape Verde had a recent 3-0 loss to Egypt but bounced back with a 2-0 win over Mauritania.
Post-Match Reflections: Botswana's win was a crucial result for their quest in the Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers.
Cape Verde's defeat brought their momentum down after a previous win.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Botswana had 75% possession and 25 shots on target, but Cape Verde couldn't capitalize.
Both teams had no sidelined players, leading to full strength lineups.
Others: The match was part of Group Stage for the Africa Cup of Nations Qualifying.
